description: Core source code of jQuery library, defining the jQuery function, prototype methods, utility functions, and internal variables.

methods.name: toArray
methods.description: Converts the jQuery object to a true array.

methods.name: get
methods.description: Retrieves the DOM element at the specified index or all elements as an array.

methods.name: pushStack
methods.description: Creates a new jQuery object from an array of elements, maintaining chainability.

methods.name: each
methods.description: Executes a callback for each element in the jQuery object.

methods.name: map
methods.description: Creates a new jQuery object by applying a callback to each element.

methods.name: slice
methods.description: Returns a subset of the matched elements as a new jQuery object.

methods.name: first
methods.description: Returns the first element in the set.

methods.name: last
methods.description: Returns the last element in the set.

methods.name: eq
methods.description: Returns the element at the specified index.

methods.name: end
methods.description: Ends the most recent filtering operation in the current chain.

methods.name: extend
methods.description: Merges the contents of two or more objects into the first object.

methods.name: globalEval
methods.description: Evaluates a script in the global context.

methods.name: camelCase
methods.description: Converts dashed strings to camelCase.

methods.name: nodeName
methods.description: Checks if an element's nodeName matches a given string.

methods.name: each (utility)
methods.description: Iterates over object or array, executing a callback.

methods.name: trim
methods.description: Removes leading and trailing whitespace from a string.

methods.name: makeArray
methods.description: Converts an array-like object into a true array.

methods.name: inArray
methods.description: Finds the index of an element within an array.

methods.name: merge
methods.description: Merges two arrays into the first array.

methods.name: grep
methods.description: Filters an array based on a callback function.

methods.name: proxy
methods.description: Binds a function to a specific context, optionally with pre-supplied arguments.

methods.name: now
methods.description: Returns the current timestamp.
